ALSO: Lines 2714-2718, the volatility multiplier context
---------------------------------------------------------
Currently passes { volatility: indicators.volatility || 0 } to createExitContract().
In ExitContractManager.createExitContract(), if volatility > 2.0 it multiplies SL by 1.2 and TP by 1.3.
This is inflating the already-tight 1m values. The threshold of 2.0 is too low for 1-minute data.

FIND (ExitContractManager.js, inside createExitContract()):
    if (context.volatility && context.volatility > 2.0) {
      contract.stopLossPercent *= 1.2;
      contract.takeProfitPercent *= 1.3;
    }

REPLACE WITH:
    // FIX 2026-02-21: Raised threshold from 2.0 to 5.0 for 1-minute data
    // On 1m candles, volatility 2.0 is normal - only widen on extreme vol
    if (context.volatility && context.volatility > 5.0) {
      contract.stopLossPercent *= 1.15;
      contract.takeProfitPercent *= 1.2;
    }
